              "learner_facing_content": "Source-supported teaching from NATP Module 10, Objective 5: Describe the circulatory system as it relates to pulse and identify the pulse sites. A. Pulse 1. Each time the heart contracts, blood is forced into the arterial system. The arterial walls expand to accept the increase in pressure; this expansion is called the pulse 2. By counting each palpated expansion of the arterial wall, the pulse rate can be determined 3. The average (adult heart beat) pulse is 60 to100 beats/minute B. Major pulse sites 1. Carotid – neck 2. Apical – left chest (taken with stethoscope)\n\nCNA scope boundary: Apply this as theory support for in-scope CNA observation, reporting, documentation, and care-plan follow-through.",
